text.section:
Unless the act or omission amounts to gross negligence or willful and wanton misconduct, a person is not civilly liable for any act or omission that affects the nature, age, condition, or packaging of the donated food if the person in good faith:
Donates food for use or distribution by a nonprofit corporation, organization, or association;
Prepares donated food for use or distribution by a nonprofit corporation, organization, or association;
Serves donated food distributed by a nonprofit corporation, organization, or association; or
Dispenses donated food distributed by a nonprofit corporation, organization, or association.
